# 📅 Plans

> Phased implementation roadmap for the Agents Relay module.

---

## Plans

### P1 Agents Relay — Foundation
**Status:** Done
**Objective:** G1, G2, G3
**Estimated Duration:** 6 weeks
**Owner:** Tooling Team

**Phase Breakdown:**

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P1.1 | Soul + Profession data model and registry | Tooling | 3 days | D1 | Done |
| P1.2 | Built-in professions (Intaker, Planner, Architect, Coder, Tester, Reviewer) | Tooling | 2 days | P1.1 | Done |
| P1.3 | Default Soul configs in `.autoforge/souls/` | Tooling | 2 days | P1.1 | Done |
| P1.4 | ModelConfig with provider abstraction and fallback chain | Tooling | 2 days | P1.1 | Done |
| P1.5 | Refactor existing Forge into reusable `AgentTurn` engine | Tooling | 3 days | P1.2 | Done |
| P1.6 | HandoffDocument schema and generation | Tooling | 3 days | D3 | Done |
| P1.7 | Context scoping: filter specs by profession | Tooling | 2 days | P1.6 | Done |
| P1.8 | Handoff compression (cheap model or rule-based) | Tooling | 2 days | P1.6 | Done |
| P1.9 | Unit tests for AgentInstance and Handoff generation | Tooling | 2 days | P1.5, P1.6 | Done |

**Risk:** Soul markdown format may need iteration once real agents use it.  
**Mitigation:** Start with simple Souls; evolve format based on first 3 real flows.

**Depends on:** G1, G2, G3, D1, D3

---

### P2 Agents Relay — Flow Engine
**Status:** Done
**Objective:** G2, G6
**Estimated Duration:** 4 weeks
**Owner:** Tooling Team

**Phase Breakdown:**

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P2.1 | FlowSpec parser (AutoDown-based DSL) | Tooling | 3 days | D2 | Empty |
| P2.2 | PipelineEngine state machine | Tooling | 3 days | D2 | Empty |
| P2.3 | Step execution: spawn agent, run turn, collect result | Tooling | 2 days | P1.5, P2.2 | Empty |
| P2.4 | Flow branching: Intaker → DIRECT vs full pipeline | Tooling | 2 days | P2.2 | Empty |
| P2.5 | Flow looping: Coder ↔ Tester with max iteration bound | Tooling | 2 days | P2.2 | Empty |
| P2.6 | Human gates: pause, notify, approve/reject/edit | Tooling | 3 days | D2 | Empty |
| P2.7 | Gate rejection routing back to drafting profession | Tooling | 2 days | P2.6 | Empty |
| P2.8 | Deterministic orchestrator unit tests | Tooling | 2 days | P2.1-P2.7 | Empty |

**Risk:** Human gate UI may add friction and slow down development.  
**Mitigation:** Allow auto-approve mode for internal dogfooding; gates mandatory for external users.

**Depends on:** G2, G6, D2, P1

---

### P3 Agents Relay — Checkpoint & Durability
**Status:** Done
**Objective:** G4
**Estimated Duration:** 3 weeks
**Owner:** Tooling Team

**Phase Breakdown:**

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P3.1 | Checkpoint data model and JSON serialization | Tooling | 2 days | D4 | Done |
| P3.2 | File manifest capture (hash, size) | Tooling | 2 days | D4 | Done |
| P3.3 | Git integration: auto-commit or diff capture | Tooling | 2 days | D4 | Done |
| P3.4 | Checkpoint save/load on disk | Tooling | 2 days | P3.1 | Done |
| P3.5 | Resume from checkpoint: restore files, ledger, state | Tooling | 3 days | P3.4 | Done |
| P3.6 | Rehydrate agent from checkpoint (no chat history) | Tooling | 2 days | P3.5 | Done |
| P3.7 | Rollback to previous checkpoint | Tooling | 2 days | P3.4 | Done |
| P3.8 | Fork run from checkpoint with different parameters | Tooling | 2 days | P3.7 | Done |
| P3.9 | Crash recovery integration tests | Tooling | 2 days | P3.5-P3.8 | Done |

**Risk:** Git auto-commit may pollute project history with checkpoint commits.  
**Mitigation:** Use a separate `autoforge-checkpoints` branch, or store diffs in checkpoint JSON without committing.

**Depends on:** G4, D4, P2

