### P6 Agents Relay — Integration & Dogfooding
**Status:** Draft
**Objective:** G1-G6
**Estimated Duration:** 2 weeks
**Owner:** Tooling Team

**Phase Breakdown:**

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P6.1 | End-to-end flow: Intake → Planner → Architect → Coder → Tester → Reviewer | Tooling | 3 days | P1-P5 | Empty |
| P6.2 | Migrate Agents module design into Ledger specs | Tooling | 2 days | P6.1 | Empty |
| P6.3 | Dogfooding: use Forge to implement P1-P5 specs | Tooling | 5 days | P6.2 | Empty |
| P6.4 | Drift detection on Agents module specs | Tooling | 2 days | P6.3 | Empty |
| P6.5 | Documentation and tutorial for custom flows | Tooling | 2 days | P6.1 | Empty |

**Risk:** Dogfooding may reveal fundamental workflow issues that require redesign.  
**Mitigation:** Schedule buffer time in P6 for iteration. Treat dogfooding as a learning exercise, not a deadline.

**Depends on:** G1, G2, G3, G4, G5, G6, P1, P2, P3, P4, P5
